  <p>*Note: パン (pan) comes from Portuguese (pão), not English. Many older loanwords in Japanese came from Portuguese and Dutch traders in the 16th-17th centuries, including ガラス (garasu, glass from Dutch) and タバコ (tabako, tobacco from Portuguese).</p>

